The paper proposes a new end-to-end question answering model that learns to aggregate answer evidence from an incomplete knowledge base and retrieved text snippets. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as entity recognition and reformulation of questions in the latent space. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and machine learning for language processing. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for knowledge acquisition and aggregation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with information retrieval and search over knowledge bases, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves learning to read and understand text, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Learning). Finally, the paper deals with knowledge bases, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases).
